GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 247
Short Title: 8-1-1 Amendments. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Zenger, Watford, and Setzer (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Energy and Public Utilities, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the
House
March 3, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO UPDATE THE UNDERGROUND UTILITY SAFETY AND DAMAGE
3 PREVENTION ACT.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 87-121 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 87-121. Facility operator responsibilities.
7 (a) An operator shall provide to the excavator the following:
8 (1) The horizontal location and description of all of the operator's facilities in the
9 area where the proposed excavation or demolition is to occur. The location
10 shall be marked by stakes, soluble paint, flags, or any combination thereof, as
11 appropriate, depending upon the conditions in the area of the proposed
12 excavation or demolition. The operator shall, when marking as provided under
13 this subdivision, use the APWA Uniform Color Code. Where practical,
14 painted surface marks shall be of adequate length to distinguish from dots. If
15 the diameter or width of the facility is greater than four inches, the dimension
16 of the facility shall be indicated at least every 50 feet in the area of the
17 proposed excavation or demolition. An operator who operates multiple
18 facilities in the area of the proposed excavation or demolition shall locate each
19 facility.
20 (1a) The operator's identity, marked as provided in subdivision (1) of this
21 subsection, in the area where the proposed excavation or demolition is to
22 occur. At a minimum, the operator's identity shall be marked at the beginning
23 point, at intervals of 200 linear feet, and at the end point of the proposed
24 excavation or demolition.
25 (2) Any other information that would assist the excavator in identifying and
26 thereby avoiding damage to the marked facilities.
27 (b) Unless otherwise provided in a written agreement between the operator and the
28 excavator, including an electronically transmitted written agreement, the operator shall provide
29 to the excavator the information required by subsection (a) of this section within the times
30 provided below:
31 (1) For a facility, within three full working days after the day notice of the
32 proposed excavation or demolition was provided to the Notification
33 Center.prior to the work start date provided by the excavator.
*H247-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) For a subaqueous facility, within 10 full working days after the day notice of
2 the proposed excavation or demolition was provided to the Notification
3 Center.
4 (3) If the operator declares an extraordinary circumstance, the times provided in
5 this subsection shall not apply.
6 (4) For an emergency request, the operator shall make an initial contact with the
7 excavator within three hours.
8 (5) For a request of an unmarked facility required by G.S. 87-122(c)(6), the
9 operator shall arrange to mark the facility within three hours from the time the
10 additional notice is received by the Notification Center.
11 …."
12 SECTION 2. G.S. 87-122 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 87-122. Excavator responsibilities.
14 (a) Before commencing any excavation or demolition operation, the person responsible
15 for the excavation or demolition shall provide or cause to be provided notice to the Notification
16 Center of his or her intent to excavate or demolish. Notice for any excavation or demolition that
17 does not involve a subaqueous facility must be given within three to 12 full working days before
18 the proposed commencement date of the excavation or demolition. not less than three full
19 working days prior to the proposed commencement date of the excavation or demolition. Notice
20 for any excavation or demolition in the vicinity of a subaqueous facility must be given within 10
21 to 20 full working days before the proposed commencement date of the excavation or demolition.
22 Notice given pursuant to this subsection shall expire 15 full working days 28 calendar days after
23 the date notice was given. No excavation or demolition may continue after this 15-day period
24 28-day period unless the person responsible for the excavation or demolition provides a
25 subsequent update notice which shall be provided in the same manner as the original notice
26 required by this subsection. When demolition of a building is proposed, the operator shall be
27 given a reasonable time in which to remove or protect the operator's facilities before the
28 demolition commences.
29 (b) The notice required by subsection (a) of this section shall, at a minimum, contain all
30 of the following:
31 (1) The name, address, and telephone number of the person providing the notice.
32 (2) The anticipated starting date of the proposed excavation or demolition.
33 (3) The anticipated duration of the proposed excavation or demolition.
34 (4) The type of proposed excavation or demolition operation to be conducted.
35 (5) The location of the proposed excavation or demolition by one of the
36 following:The area of locate of the proposed excavation or demolition, which
37 shall be limited to an area the excavator reasonably believes may be completed
38 within 28 calendar days from the work start date and does not include any
39 areas where the excavation or demolition has been completed and accepted by
40 the authorities having jurisdiction. The area of locate is also limited to one of
41 the following:
42 a. A single parcel that may exceed 1/4 mile in linear length identified by
43 a single address.
44 b. The lesser of five adjoining parcels identified by addresses, not to
45 exceed 1/4 mile in linear length or an area not to exceed 1/4 mile in
46 linear length.
47 (6) Whether or not explosives are to be used in the proposed excavation or
48 demolition.
49 (c) An excavator shall comply with the following:
50 …
