1 (10) The excavator shall not use mechanized nonmechanized equipment within 24
2 inches a 24-inch circumference of a facility that is an oil, petroleum products,
3 or highly volatile liquid pipeline system, a gas transmission line, or an electric
4 transmission line unless the facility operator has consented to the use in
5 writing and the operator's representative is on site during the use of the
6 mechanized equipment. Within the tolerance zone of a pipeline system, the
7 excavator shall use safe excavation practices, such as hand digging or
8 potholing. For purposes of this subdivision, the term "oil, petroleum products,
9 or highly volatile liquid pipeline system" has the same meaning as the term
10 "pipeline system" in Title 49 C.F.R. § 195.2, the term "gas transmission line"
11 has the same meaning as the term "transmission line" in Title 49 C.F.R. §
12 192.3, and the term "electric transmission line" has the same meaning as the
13 term "transmission line" in G.S. 62-100(7)."
14 SECTION 3. G.S. 87-124 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 87-124. Exemptions.
16 The notice requirements in G.S. 87-122(a) and G.S. 87-122(b) do not apply to the following:
17 (1) An excavation or demolition performed by the owner of a single-family
18 residential property on his or her own land that does not encroach on any
19 operator's right-of-way, easement, or permitted use.
20 (2) An excavation or demolition performed by the owner of a single-family
21 residential property on his or her own land that encroaches on any operator's
22 right-of-way, easement, or permitted use that is performed with
23 nonmechanized equipment.
24 (3) An excavation or demolition that involves the tilling of soil for agricultural or
25 gardening purposes.purposes that encroaches on any operator's right-of-way,
26 easement, or permitted use and is less than 12 inches in depth.
27 (4) An excavation or demolition for agricultural purposes, as defined in
28 G.S. 106-581.1, performed on property that does not encroach on any
29 operator's right-of-way, easement, or permitted use.
30 (5) An excavation by an operator or surveyor operator, surveyor, or an operator
31 or surveyor's contractor with nonmechanized equipment for the following
32 purposes:
33 a. Locating for a valid notification request or for the minor repair,
34 connection, or routine maintenance of an existing facility or survey
35 pin.
36 b. Probing underground to determine the extent of gas or water
37 migration.
38 (6) An excavation or demolition performed when those responsible for routine
39 maintenance of a right-of-way or any other governmental entity are
40 performing, with labor on their permanent payroll, maintenance activities
41 within the right-of-way. for the purpose of maintenance activities within the
42 right-of-way. Maintenance activities shall include emergency replacement of
43 signs critical for maintaining safety or reshaping of shoulders and ditches to
44 the original road profile. Maintenance activities do not include the initial
45 installation of traffic signs, traffic control equipment, guardrails, or drainage
46 structures. The provisions of this subdivision do not apply when the
47 excavation or demolition is performed by a contractor acting on behalf of a
48 person or entity responsible for routine maintenance of a right-of-way or on
49 behalf of any other governmental entity.right-of-way.
50 (7) An excavation or demolition performed by a railroad entirely on land which
51 the railroad owns or operates or, in the event of an emergency, on adjacent
